Notable Locations.Estates & Lodges:
* [[Bleys Hard]], an estate of the [[Bleyshar]] family.{{Cite dragon/406/Eye on the Realms: Xraunrarr Will Triumph|6}}
* [[Bryargates]], a fortified [[Bryarn]] estate just south of the King's Forest.{{Cite web/Candlekeep forum/Questions for Ed Greenwood (2009)/House Bryarn}}
* [[Dimswart Manor]], home of the sage [[Dimswart]].
* [[Goldfeather Manor]], the old forest estate of the [[Goldfeather]] family.
* [[Stag Steads]], a luxurious hunting lodge hidden in the King's Forest.
* [[Taverton Hall]], the prestigious Northbank estate of the [[Paertrover]] family.
* [[Thornthar]], a royal estate kept for retired servants.{{Cite web/Candlekeep forum/Questions for Ed Greenwood (2013)/Royal Servants of Cormyr}}
* [[Thulser's Lodge]], a royal estate that treated diseased [[Purple Dragons|Purple]] and [[Blue Dragons]].{{Cite web/Candlekeep forum/Questions for Ed Greenwood (2013)/Elderly & Retirement}}
* [[Wyrmdown]], the expansive country estate of House [[Haldoneir]].

Notable Locations.Ruins:
* [[Blackstone (building)|Blackstone]], the destroyed estate of the [[Theresparin]] family.
* [[Coryl's Lair]], a ruined seatower off the coast near Marsember that became home to the [[vampire]] [[mermaid]] [[Coryl Erazem]].{{Cite dungeon/113/Practical Magic|40-44}}
* [[Crownpost]], a Purple Dragons stronghold destroyed by a storm and an army of magical creatures.
* The [[Haunted Halls]], the fortified underground hideout of [[Rivior]] turned legendary adventuring site.
* The [[House on the Cliff]], the most powerful temple of [[Umberlee]] in the Realms, destroyed in the Time of Troubles.
* [[Jarthroon]], an ancient holding on the [[Dragonmere]] conquered by King [[Duar Obarskyr]].{{Cite dragon/279/The New Adventures of Volo: Lost Treasures of Cormyr, Part 2|82-83}}
* [[Meliyekur’s Magical Museum]], an estate turned into a museum and then a ruin, used by the [[Women of the Woods]].
* [[Rivior's Keep]], a surface fortress built by Rivior.
* [[Turnstone]], a long-gone road-fort north of Immersea.{{Cite dragon/280/The New Adventures of Volo: Lost Treasures of Cormyr, Part 3|87}}
* [[Zundle]], a razed village that became a byword for foolishness.
